<br>&nbsp;
<ul>
<li>
<b><font size=+3>Seeheim model: (refer to <a href="f2.htm">figure 2</a>)</font></b></li>
</ul>

<ol>
<ol>
<li>
<b><font size=+2>Presentation -- <u>lexical aspects</u> of the interaction.</font></b></li>

<li>
<b><font size=+2>Dialogue Control -- <u>syntactic aspects</u> of the interaction
and is responsible for the dynamics of the application.</font></b></li>

<li>
<b><font size=+2>Application Interface -- <u>layer of adaptation</u> for
the non-interactive application kenel to conform to the envisaged style
of interaction.</font></b></li>
</ol>
</ol>

<ul>
<li>
<b><font size=+3>Drawback:</font></b></li>
</ul>

<ol>
<ol>
<li>
<b><font size=+2>No clue on how to integrate the application with the <u>existing
toolkit</u> it is targeted to.</font></b></li>

<li>
<b><font size=+2>Not acknowledge that the <u>weight</u> of the three components
will vary according to different type of application.</font></b></li>

<li>
<b><font size=+2>No relationship with an <u>exisiting software design method</u>
is given.</font></b></li>
</ol>
</ol>

